Orlando Bezerra de Menezes Airport (IATA: JDO, ICAO: SBJU) also known as Juazeiro do Norte Airport, is the airport serving Juazeiro do Norte, Brazil. It is named after a local politician and entrepreneur.
It is operated by AENA.


== History ==
The airport has been operated by Infraero since 2002 but on March 15, 2019 AENA won a 30-year concession to operate the airport.


== Airlines and destinations ==


== Access ==
The airport is located 6 km (4 mi) from downtown Juazeiro do Norte.


